16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 11-403.1, is
18 amended to read as follows:
19 Section 11-403.1. A. Any person convicted of failure to yield
20 a right-of-way and who causes a fatality or serious great bodily
21 injury, as defined in Section 11-904 of this title, as a result of
22 such violation may shall, in addition to any other fine or penalty,
23 be assessed a fee in an the amount not exceeding One Thousand
24 Dollars ($1,000.00) of Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00) to be
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1022 Page 1
1 depo sited in the Motorcycle Safety and Education Program Revolving
2 Fund established in Section 40-123 of this title. Any person
3 convicted of failure to yield a right-of-way and who causes a
4 serious bodily injury as a result of such violation may, in addition
5 to any other fine or penalty, be assessed a fee in the amount of
6 Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00) to be deposited in the Motorcycle
7 Safety and Education Program Revolving Fund. For the purposes of
8 this section, a serious bodily injury is an injury that is serious
9 in nature but does not quite rise to the level of a great bodily
10 injury or a fatality.
11 The monies deposited as provided in this section subsection
12 shall be used to promote public awareness of the dangers of driving
13 while under the influence of alcohol or any controlled substance and
14 to promote motorcycle safety and defensive driving for youth.
15 B. In addition to the fees provided in subsection A of this
16 section, the court may impose additional penalties, including:
17 1. A remedial driving course;
18 2. A loss of driver license for ninety (90) days; or
19 3. A payment of restitution of no less than Three Thousand
20 Dollars ($3,000.00), but no more than Ten Thousand Dollars
21 ($10,000.00).
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
